Instructions for SSO with Pocket ID

Note that if you already have a login on Endurain, the email address must match that with your SSO account otherwise Endurain will create a new user with the SSO email address.
You'll need the FQDN of your OIDC provier and of your Endurain installation.

Log into Pocket ID and head to "Administration" and "OIDC Clients"
Select "Add OIDC client"
Name - "Endurain"
Client Launch URL - the FQDN of your installation of Endurain e.g. https://endurain.mydomain.com
Callback URLS - https://endurain.mydomain.com/api/v1/public/idp/callback/pocket-id

Click save and make a note of your Client ID and Secret.

In Endurain, head over to "Settings" and "Identity Providers". Select "Add Identity Provider" and "Custom"
Provider Name: Pocket ID
Slug: pocket-id
Provider Type: OIDC
Issuer URL: the FQDN of your Pocket ID instance (no trailing /)
Client ID: from above
Client secret: from above
Scopes: openid profile email



Instructions for SSO with Tailscale TSIDP

Log into your instance of TSIDP and select "Add new client"
Client Name: "Endurain"
Redirect URIs: https://endurain.mydomain.com/api/v1/public/idp/callback/tsidp

Click "create client" and make a note of the client ID and secret.

In Endurain, head over to "Settings" and "Identity Providers". Select "Add Identity Provider" and "Custom"
Provider Name: TSIDP
Slug: tsidp
Provider Type: OIDC
Issuer URL: the FQDN of your Pocket ID instance (no trailing /)
Client ID: from above
Client secret: from above
Scopes: openid profile email
